@startuml m1_phase1_working_env_activity
' Research artifact (project-researcher) — Phase 1 activity-flow requirements.
' Shows one scenario tick end-to-end: bench emission -> V2X_Comm decode ->
' ADA situation assessment -> IVI warning. ADA output is mocked in Phase 1;
' Phases 2-4 + 6 replace it with real perceived data; Phase 5 consumes it.
title Phase 1 Activity Flow — scenario injection, decode, awareness, warning

|#DDEBF7|Bench Scenario Player|
start
:Load scenario script + impairment config (externalized);
repeat
  :Advance simulated trajectories of B and C by one tick;
  :Update ego trajectory and publish ego GNSS feed;
  :Build B's V2X messages — CAM (B state) + CPM (B's perceived object C) with StationID, generationDeltaTime, sender reference position;
  :Encode ASN.1 UPER (asn1tools, official ETSI modules);
  if (Impairment: drop this message?) then (yes)
    :Log drop (reproducible seed);
  else (no)
    :Apply configured delay / jitter;
    :Send UDP datagram into ego network (bench-to-ego channel);
    |#E2EFDA|Ego V2X_Comm|
    :Receive datagram (thin transport adapter);
    :Strip envelope and UPER-decode payload (asn1tools; GN/BTP deferred to adapter upgrade path);
    if (Decode and field validation OK?) then (no)
      :Log and discard;
    else (yes)
      :Publish decoded V2X PDU to ADA (sender GNSS position, perceived object C, timestamps);
      |#FFF2CC|Ego ADA|
      :Read ego position (GnssProvider);
      :Update environment model — B as direct neighbour (CAM), C as relayed perceived object (CPM);
      :Compute relative geometry d_AB and d_BC, then compose d_AC;
      :Assess situation — two vehicles ahead, C occluded by B (NLOS);
      :Emit warning event (Phase 1: mocked risk label — real data arrives via Phases 2-4 + 6);
      |#FCE4D6|Ego IVI Display|
      :Render BEV + occluded-vehicle warning (2D in M1, 3D optional);
    endif
  endif
  |#DDEBF7|Bench Scenario Player|
repeat while (Scenario still running?) is (yes)
->no;
stop

@enduml
